<s> I have been experimenting with Dia (actually the windows version: http://dia-installer.sourceforge.net/ ) and this is meant to produce SVG files, which it does, but they start with !DOCTYPE svg PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD SVG 20000802//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/2000/CR-SVG-20000802/DTD/svg-20000802.dtd" Which is not the 1.0 scheme as described on the SVG page: When I put the images into Amaya they come up almost invisible.  </s>
<s> I have tried changing the header in one file to agree with the 1.0 spec to fudge this, but it still displays incorrectly.  </s>
<s> So the question is: "is the bug in Amaya, in Dia, or are they using incompatible SVG specs?".  </s>
<s> To answer that I need a validator for SVG, but I cannot find one.  </s>
<s> Is this because there isn't one, or have I just not found it yet?  </s>
